# Git Commit

Agent may run `git commit -m "..."` after user approves message. **To avoid trailers:** Cursor Settings → Agent → Attribution → OFF.

# Push

Agent runs `git push` **only when user requests** AND **log has no trailer**.

Before push: agent MUST run `git log -3 --format=%B`. If trailer exists → push FORBIDDEN, only soft reset allowed.

# RED FLAG – Trailer in Log

- Agent: only `git reset --soft HEAD~1` allowed, push FORBIDDEN
- User: Cursor Settings → Agent → Attribution → OFF, recommit
- Then: agent can push (if user requests and log is clean)

## FORBIDDEN

**NEVER** push when trailer in log. **NEVER** modify git config.
